column5: For people who know what fishing is like at Binbrook you will like this ..... you don't see this very much there......  19" walleye
Thats some nice fish ya got there TBC. That would make anyones day Thanks for sharing  Paul
Wow, what a great catch!!!!   Congratz
Nice! Was it busy there? I've been thinking about heading there verry soon
Nice catch TBC.  Now if I can only get another one to nibble,its been a long time
I've never fishing Binbrooke but that's a nice Walleye.
They all count and that's a nice fish. Well done.
Thaxz alot guys .... It's not a big fish but for this lake it's like 1 in 1000 to get a welleye
more like one in a million  The last one ive seen caught was in the late eighties. My lure and my bud using it! 8 plus pounds. Thats a nice one you have there TBC!
does that lake have bluegill's? I only ask as a lure idea to try to get more...
Yeah but not alot .... You can fish all week and use all the lures you have and you still won't get a welleye from there I don't know y that is but it is lol there are not that meny eyes in there
Check your PM in a few min...
Been there a couple of times, never saw one of those! Nice fish! Cheers, Dave
oh they are there and interested in following your bait, but never to bite  fish finder photo of what I had to deal with on numerous ocassions!
